"{\"uid\": \"express.co.uk-sport-othersport-1930598-Olympics-2024-Leon-Marchand-Michael-Phelps\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  Leon Marchand madeOlympicshistory on Wednesday night by becoming the first swimmer to win the 200m butterfly and breaststroke in the same session.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 148, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7, \"end\": 15, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"score\": 0.9999999904212018, \"rank\": 7.430460359839968e-09, \"text\": \"Marchand\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q11774891\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Frenchman lifted the roof off Paris' La Defense Arena twice by winning both races in the space of two hours, achieving a feat that even Michael Phelps did not attempt.\", \"from\": 149, \"to\": 320, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 183, \"end\": 188, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999863576, \"rank\": 1.3760343466803067e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 289, \"end\": 303, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2851171704864335e-50, \"text\": \"Michael Phelps\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Marchand had already won gold in the 400m individual medley before adding a second and third in miraculous fashion at his home Games.\", \"from\": 322, \"to\": 455, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 22-year-old first stormed to victory in the 200m butterfly, setting a new Olympic Record of 1:51.21, pipping Hungary's Kristof Milak, the previous record holder.\", \"from\": 457, \"to\": 622, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 570, \"end\": 577, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\", \"score\": 0.9381150339037838, \"rank\": 0.06596732127432384, \"text\": \"Hungary\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\"}, {\"begin\": 588, \"end\": 593, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milak\", \"score\": 0.9266808015700746, \"rank\": 0.07912020628441764, \"text\": \"Milak\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milak\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milak\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Pick up your ultimate guide to the Olympics!\", \"from\": 624, \"to\": 668, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Going for Gold provides the day-by-day rundown of what's on and when.\", \"from\": 669, \"to\": 738, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Clickhereto buy.\", \"from\": 739, \"to\": 755, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After a brief break, Marchand re-emerged to an explosive ovation and produced an even more impressive showing in the 200m breaststroke.\", \"from\": 757, \"to\": 892, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He not only won his second gold medal in as many hours, but he set another Olympic Record of 2:05.85 to beat Australian favourite Zac Stubblety-Cook.\", \"from\": 894, \"to\": 1043, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1003, \"end\": 1013, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9995131949285468, \"rank\": 0.00020746694586028624, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 1024, \"end\": 1042, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zac_Stubblety-Cook\", \"score\": 0.9999995230460855, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Zac Stubblety-Cook\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zac_Stubblety-Cook\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zac_Stubblety-Cook\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Two gold medals in as many hours - a tally more than most do not achieve in their entire swimming career.\", \"from\": 1045, \"to\": 1150, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"France's poster boy has lived up to the hype.\", \"from\": 1151, \"to\": 1196, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1151, \"end\": 1157, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.5437889017922481, \"rank\": 0.6930400423533726, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Phelps was no stranger to success, winning 28 Olympic medals across his iconic career, 23 of them gold.\", \"from\": 1198, \"to\": 1301, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1198, \"end\": 1204, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\", \"score\": 0.9999999878923519, \"rank\": 1.2106973478574671e-08, \"text\": \"Phelps\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But never did he achieve this feat.\", \"from\": 1302, \"to\": 1337, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He will be proud of the efforts of Marchand, who is coached in the United States by Phelps' former mentor, Bob Bowman.\", \"from\": 1339, \"to\": 1457, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1374, \"end\": 1382, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"score\": 0.9999999904212018, \"rank\": 7.430460359839968e-09, \"text\": \"Marchand\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q11774891\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\"}, {\"begin\": 1406, \"end\": 1419, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9989670789068277, \"rank\": 0.